From bfecfc56a318cb5c72d3140e24d3d13f2028db90 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jernej Skrabec <jernej.skrabec@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 08:47:03 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 19/27] media: cedrus: Add VP9 decoding support

The VP9 decoder shares the H.265 engine slot and register bank on the
H616. Register layout and the probability table DMA buffer format were
reverse engineered from the vendor libawvp9HwAL.so blob: the buffer
holds a tile entry list at the start, a packed probability block at
offset 0x4000, the entropy counter write-back region at 0x4b00 and the
segment ID map at 0x8000. Probability adaptation follows the spec
refresh_probs() flow using the v4l2 vp9 helpers, with the counters
provided by the hardware.

Signed-off-by: Jernej Skrabec <jernej.skrabec@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_019m4MPFATiJUdhA7nbwr9pk
